Hello

The Library domain is for putting AXIOM values from different domains int=
o one=20
Keyed-Acess-File. It's a useful way for transmitting values from one AXIO=
M=20
session to another. Your first session should have created a directory ca=
lled=20
data.KAF containing a file called index.KAF and in this file would be a=20
Lisp-readable representation of the values you put in it. Do you get thes=
e=20
files at the end of the first session?
The second session must be started at the same working directory as the f=
irst.=20
Is there a directory called data.KAF when you start the second session?

Themos

