> The internal form of Maxima expressions is a Lisp s-expression, which
> you can see using the ?print function.  For example,
>         sin(x)/x-x-1
> is represented as
>        ((MPLUS SIMP) -1
>                                    ((MTIMES SIMP) -1 $X)
>                                    ((MTIMES SIMP) ((MEXPT SIMP) $X -1)
>                                    ((%SIN SIMP) $X)))


